# Room Chat

A real-time chat application built with Node.js, Express, and Socket.IO. Users can create or join chat rooms by entering a room code and participate in group conversations.

# Features

- Create or join chat rooms with custom codes
- Set maximum number of members per room (1-10)
- Real-time messaging with timestamps
- Automatic room cleanup when empty
- Responsive web interface

# Prerequisites

- Node.js (version 14 or higher)
- npm (comes with Node.js)

# Installation

1. Clone the repository or download the project files.
2. Navigate to the project directory:
   ```
   cd /home/saikumar/room-chat
   ```
3. Install dependencies:
   ```
   npm install
   ```

# Running the Application

1. Start the server:
   ```
   node server.js
   ```
2. Open your web browser and go to:
   ```
   http://localhost:3000
   ```

The server will start on port 3000 by default. You can change the port by setting the `PORT` environment variable:
```
PORT=8080 node server.js
```

# Usage

1. Enter your name (optional, defaults to "Guest")
2. Enter a room code or click "Create Room" to generate one
3. Set the maximum number of members (1-10, defaults to 2)
4. Click "Create Room" or "Join Room"
5. Start chatting! Messages will appear in real-time for all room members

# Project Structure

- `server.js` - Main server file handling Socket.IO connections and room management
- `public/index.html` - Frontend HTML interface
- `public/app.js` - Frontend JavaScript for chat functionality
- `package.json` - Project dependencies and metadata

# Dependencies

- Express: Web framework for serving static files
- Socket.IO: Real-time bidirectional communication
